name: Yellow Bar
review_text:
This place bans loyal customers without cause. I‚Äôve been going to this bar since 2008, never caused a problem, never had an issue‚Äîyet I was arbitrarily banned, likely due to personal dislikes or sheer arrogance from the new management. No explanation, no justification, just an abuse of power. Meanwhile, I have several female friends  who were actually harassed by aggressive groups inside this bar and had to leave for their safety and one had her phone stolen‚Äîyet management turned a blind eye.
Even worse, a former bartender was removed from his role after multiple accusations of inappropriate behavior toward female customers. And yet, despite his history, he still freely enters the bar as a customer and skips the line, and even gets inside the hostel like he owns the place.They don't really care about getting rid of troublemakers; they ban people they simply don‚Äôt like. If that‚Äôs the kind of place you want to support, be my guest. Otherwise, avoid this bully-style establishment at all costs.
owner_answer:
Eliphas, qui √® il manager che ti scrive. Sai bene perch√© ti √® stato negato l‚Äôingresso ormai quasi due anni fa : il tuo comportamento nei confronti di alcune nostre ospiti √® stato inaccettabile e irrispettoso e noi siamo anche diventati Punti Viola. √à difficile comprendere la tua insistenza nel lasciare recensioni false e nel presentarti ogni sera fuori dal nostro locale per importunare il nostro staff.
Abbiamo raccolto diverse testimonianze e ti abbiamo gi√† avvisato pi√π volte che, se la situazione fosse continuata, avremmo intrapreso azioni legali. Il rispetto per le nostre clienti √® una priorit√† assoluta, e non tollereremo atteggiamenti che possano comprometterne la sicurezza. Puoi scrivere tutte le recensioni false e negative lo preferiremo comunque ad avere persone irrispettose. 
Ti invitiamo a riflettere sul concetto di consenso e sul fatto che un ‚Äúno‚Äù deve sempre essere rispettato. Se questa situazione dovesse proseguire, saremo costretti ad agire per vie legali.

name: Yellow Bar
review_text:
GIRLS please READ and be careful!!! I went to this bar with my friend since we were in Rome for vacation. The staff very kind and the ambiance as well, BUT there was this group of boys who wouldn‚Äôt stop HARASSING me and my friend, my friend got really angry because they were not understanding the clear NO. When my friend finally yelled at them asking them to leave us, they just went laughing and making fun of us just because we rejected them. A couple that was next to us tried to defend us and we told the guards but they DID NOTHING, just told us to chill. Which is not OKAY and something I never experienced in Europe before, usually when someone is clearly HARASSING girls the guard should ask them to leave not ask us to chill. Unbelievable!! The people at the bar and the ones coordinating the party were so nice, sadly I would not be coming back to that place and honestly made fear nightlife in Rome in general. PLEASE girls be careful!!! These are the type of guys who do not take a NO for an answer and the guards seemed to be their friends. Would NOT hang out there or recommended to any girl, please be careful, specially if you‚Äôre young üòî I really can‚Äôt stress this enough. They even TOUCHED us, were trying to grab us and forcing us to talk or dance. On our way out, we met other people and they told us this bar has had issues before because of the same thing. This is not new for them and they did nothing. Please if you go be careful of your drink as well. But honestly I would totally skip this bar, it was very unpleasant for us and to think that could be worse for others girls and they are just ask to CHILL breaks my heart. Be safe out there.

Response:

As I said before everyone member of the staff was very kind, and they did talk to us on our way out. However, we were not going to stay next to a group that was harassing us just a minute ago, as much as there was a security person watching over, it‚Äôs just uncomfortable and upsetting.

I understand that everyone has the right to be at the bar and have a good time, but when someone is being disrespectful towards others that person should be removed for others people safety. Because it could be us in that moment and later other girls.

I understand you try to create a safe environment but I‚Äôm afraid that‚Äôs no possible if you let people who are harassing get away it, because that‚Äôs what happened. We left and they just got away with it and they‚Äôll probably come back and do the same thing to other girls because they know they just get a warning and that‚Äôs it.
owner_answer:
Dear Vanessa, We‚Äôre really sorry to hear about your experience and completely understand how upsetting it must have been. Your safety and comfort are always our top priorities.  
As soon as our staff was made aware of the situation, Mel, our manager, and Lorenzo, our security supervisor, stepped in right away. We even assigned someone near the group of guys to ensure nothing else happened and to keep an eye on the situation.  You decided to leave and we totally get this. 
It‚Äôs upsetting to hear that this incident impacted your view of our Bar, especially since we work hard to 
create a safe and respectful space for everyone. Many of our female guests choose us because they feel secure here, and we‚Äôre proud of the work we do to uphold that standard.  
Please know that we take incidents like this very seriously and acted immediately, in line with our policy that doesn‚Äôt tolerate any form of harassment. We believe every guest has the right to feel safe while having fun, and we‚Äôre deeply committed to that mission.  
We truly appreciate your feedback and will use it to improve further. If you‚Äôd like to talk more about this, we‚Äôre here and happy to listen‚Äîfeel free to reach out via email or in person.  
Thanks again for sharing your experience.

name: Yellow Bar
review_text:
I tried this place three times while I was staying at the hostel.

1: I had gotten a pizza from another establishment to go and was hoping to eat it at the bar if I ordered a drink. I was firmly and immediately denied service that I could not bring outside food in. I was referred to as "bro" in a condescending manner during this. It was very quiet with not many people inside so I didn't see the issue but whatever. Kick to the teeth is the next day I go for a burger and I see a couple guys at the bar eating a pizza from a different place and having beers. Talk about double standards.

2: Went with a buddy to get a Spritz, was serviced quickly and got a table right away. Issue I had here was even after stating that I was with the hostel they did not ask to see my bracelet nor gave me the advertised discount on my drink. Thought to myself whatever, not worth trying to argue over it.

3: Walked past and saw that they had live music and decorated for Halloween. Unfortunately as soon as I entered the bar the guy got off stage and didn't have any more sets, which I thought strange as it was 19:30 at the time. Oh well, my loss. So I stand and wait to be serviced at the front bar for a few minutes making eye contact with the servers but no one is acknowledging me. Just as I'm about to leave someone finally comes by. I place my order for a burger and hand over my "free drink" coupon I got from the hostel. This time I make sure to show that I have my hostel bracelet. Even still, they charge me full price again!

So from my experience, I did not feel welcomed in the bar. It felt like because I didn't speak Italian well or that I didn't look the part that I was being ostracized. Maybe it's because I'm not in my early 20's or female. The food was okay nothing to rave about, and beer was good.

Yellow Bar put a sour note on my trip to Rome and I don't recommend it even for the convenience of its location to the hostel. It's a bar that is trying to be run like a club. Uncomfortable treatment and neglect by wait staff. Compliments to the cooks who were the only ones to service me with a smile! 2/5

Dear Nancy,

Thanks for leaving us a review. I'm glad to hear that you had great experience with us not only back in 2021 but also on your first night this time. Yellowsquare Management

Highly recommended

name: Yellow Bar
review_text:
I am a 35yo solo traveler who had a 12h overnight in Rome.

Yellowbar was one of the few places listed with "live music" but this Friday it did not.

I had two duffelbags and failed to find a place to store them at the Roma airport.

Unlucky / lucky for me you cannot bring bags inside the bar (totally makes sense) - so they let me into the hostel across the street they also own and I got a locker there.

I hung out inside solo and people watched. Would be cool with friends for sure.

Stayed til about closing as I needed to catch the 430am train back to Roma airport

At the bnb to get my bags - I found a group of friends jamming out and it was one of the best night experiences I've had.

So in tandem the yellowbar and yellow square (the hostel they also own) I feel is the move. You also get discounts at the bar with a wrist band.

The bouncers never checked me lingering long to grab my bags and other non hostel residents were in the group hanging out too.

Def worth the stress of taking the last train into Rome and first train out to the airport haha.

Photos are in the hostel

review_text:
I was there during peak period. Bit too much of a disjointed experience unfortunately.

A small-ish venue, karaoke in the back half of the bar and good part of the floorspace between front and back taken up by what seems the wrong kind of (cafe style) furniture. Could easily gain minimum half a star rating just giving slightly more thought to floorspace. Soo many people forced to either feel like they're in a bit of a void in the front half of the bar while the back half carried the vibe of the bar. Reasonable value for money (not amazing though). Security had quite a wierd way of instructing or assisting anyone who wanted to step out for a smoke. After a certain cutoff time in the evening everyone outside forced to become a lineup for entry. Nothing overly wrong with that; it just isn't very clear to customers what the expectation is especially for a hostel bar where unknowing travellers will frequent. As for payments... Can't recall if it was cash only/card only or combination. In my time there I didn't see an ATM though. Decent draught beer. Not a huge selection but it is a hostel bar not a speciality ale house. The variety when it came to spirits didn't seem super extensive either but the usual suspects were covered.

name: Yellow Bar
review_text:
per la prima volta in vita mia, senza motivo, un buttafuori ha deciso che non potevo rientrare dalla pausa sigaretta (all'inizio forse pensava che fossi appena arrivato e mi ha detto: siamo in chiusura).
Gli altri due volevano farmi rientrare e mi hanno provato ad aiutare, ma ovviamente quello coi problemi era il capo. Mi ha detto che ho esagerato con l'alcol, io gli ho fatto notare che non era vero e ho bevuto una sola birra. a quel punto non aveva pi√π niente da dire e ha iniziato a dire agli altri di mandarmi via. Nella vergogna totale, nessuno si √® mosso e sono rimasto li, per√≤ non mi hanno fatto rientrare nonostante avessi il biglietto. p.s. si vede nellla foto quello che ha creato il problema.
Edit: Risposta: Non c'√® stato nessun rispetto nei miei confronti! sono stato discriminato e cacciato come se per l'appunto fossi uno che mette a rischio la sicurezza di qualcun altro, quando invece diverse persone possono testimoniare che non √® cos√¨, inclusi gli altri due ragazzi che lavoravano alla sicurezza quella sera. Edit: Spero Ultima Risposta: era evidente a tutti che non ero alterato ne ubriaco, altrimenti se ne sarebbe accorto almeno uno degli altri due che invece mi hanno fatto entrare. Capisco che lanciare false accuse e negare la verit√† possa aiutare per la reputazione, ma √® abbastanza disgustoso.
owner_answer: Ciao Alex, Abbiamo notato che hai ripostato la recensione per la terza volta.  La nostra risposta non cambia: non facciamo entrare persone troppo alterate o ubriache per la sicurezza dei nostri ospiti. Quindi un motivo c'era. For the first time in my life, for no reason, a bouncer decided that I could not come back from the cigarette break (at the beginning maybe he thought I had just arrived and he said to me: we are closing).
The other two wanted to get me back and tried to help, but obviously that with the problems was the boss.He told me I exaggerated with alcohol, I pointed out that it was not true and I drank only one beer.At that point he had nothing more to say and started telling others to send me away.In total shame, nobody moved and I remained there, but they didn't make me come back despite having the ticket.P.S.You can see in the photo what the problem created.
Edit: Answer: There was no respect for me!I was discriminated against and chased as if I were one who puts someone else at risk, when several people can testify that it is not so, including the other two guys who worked on safety that evening.Edit: I hope the last answer: it was evident to everyone that I was not altered drunk, otherwise at least one of the other two would have noticed that instead made me enter.I understand that stinging false accusations and denying the truth can help for reputation, but it is quite disgusting.

when I travel I always do a review I could not do it.

name: Yellow Bar
review_text:
Where do I start! Honestly the best hostel I have ever stayed in, it is the most friendly, welcoming, social and fun place! Everyone we met was absolutely lovely, and I definately made some friends for life here!

The hostel itself was incredibly clean, and had a lot to offer! I stayed in a 4 bed room, with a shared bathroom outside the room. There were also mirrors and hairdryers outside the door. My only complaint was how creaky the beds were, a single movement and the whole thing screamed! However, it was a very central position, close to the Termini station and major landmarks. All of us in our room enjoyed late night walks to the colosseum which was about 20 mins away! Also, the Yellow almost has its own road, with a barbers, hire centre, restaurant, bar, club and other amenities (kitchen, games room, etc.), all of which had an incredible atmosphere of everyone wanting a good time! The bar and club have such a buzzing energy every evening.

Although we didn't see much of the staff, when checking in, everyone was so helpful and friendly! We spent a couple evenings in the bar and club, again, all were lovely! Had breakfast in the bar a couple mornings, the guy who brought it to us was very smiley, chatty and friendly!

Never would I have thought a hostel could be so great...I couldn't recommend this place more, and can't wait to go back in the future! Definitely made my time in Rome even more enjoyable.
owner_answer: Wow, thank you so much for such a detailed and sweet feedback! We're proud to know you had a good time staying at the YellowSquare and we will definitely be waiting for our next visit! Cheers!

First of all, it is a bar owned by a hostel but it's across the street meaning locals and foreigners are expected to be found.

Secondly the vibe is super social and you could go alone and make good friends in an instant.

Thirdly the prices for beer are quite nice as you have these 7% beers for 4(?) Euros which is a good price in a city like rome.

And on top of all that you have live music untill about twelve and after the dj starts playing in the basement which is wicked fun!

Definitely check this place out, and I can't say how it holds up during the day as I was there only in the evening/night. The door closes at about 3 am and inside it closes at about 5am.

review_text: It was an awful experience this last night. I was with my sister going to the bar and she was blocked to get inside by the security men because of the way she was dressed. Aperently for his taste it was too reveling. We called the manager which explained that they do that to avoid sexual harassment and problems inside the bar. Again... in this sexist society the fault is always the women? The men can‚Äôt control themselves and the fault is the women? It was a shocking moment for all of us. I never saw anything like this in any bar, anyplace around the world. Medival times? When you see a woman in trouble you help her, you don‚Äôt attack or repress them!
owner_answer:
We are really sorry you felt offended by our suggestion. Even though we are an absolutely open-minded organisation, we understand that socially speaking there are still issues with the way women and men dress in public and we wanted to avoid any troubles at any cost. Our security staff only suggested her to cover herself a bit more and never intended to offend anyone. We are always on top of any possible confrontation between our customers regardless gender. Though, it is important to mention that she was never blocked, instead she disagreed to our advice and still accessed without any problem as we do not discriminate anyone.
Once again we apologise if this was offensive to you and your sister but we just wanted to ensure her safety.

review_text: We were promised that we could check in by 13:30, but were not pleased to find out that we actually couldn't untill 14:30.When the check in time was finally in sight, we had to wait another twenty minutes to actually get checked in. When we arrived at our room by 14:55, the cleaning ladies were still working on the room even though the previous guest had already checked out before 10:00. There are nu plugs in the bathroom (except for one, which is only allowed to be used for shaving machines. Duvets were not covered in sheets, nor were there available for them. Every evening we heard quite loud music from what we suspected was the bar, which is right next to our building. The plugs in our bunk beds worked in a very odd way, which caused my sisters phone not to be charged in the morning. Apart from all above, we had a very pleasant stay in our hostel. Nice guests, enthousiastic staff! We liked the bunk beds, we still had privacy even though we were staying in a 4 people bedroom. Very nice to have towels and bedsheets offered and find a hairdryer in the bathroom.

review_text: This bar was one the best hostel bar I've been to in Europe. They have great food, reasonably priced drinks, and give guests 20% off if you book directly through their website. They are all happy to have a conversation with you (unless they're packed, which is understandable) and truly go out of their way to make you feel welcome. Be sure to tip them, it will play heavily in your favor. Highly recommend this hostel for the bar alone. Had an awesome time hanging out here every night I was in Rome.

review_text: Stayed here for a couple nights, and had a good experience. The staff are friendly and helpful, they gave us great recommendations for food and transportation tips. The dorm beds were comfy, our room was facing the street so it was loud at night, but not an issue if you bring ear plugs. The two things that could be improved- the hostel does NOT wash the blanket on the bed. I was in the room when they switched the bed sheets, and all they did was refold the blanket, which is disgusting. Those blankets need to be washed... and secondly, the wifi is awful! The wifi was very spotty in the room.

review_text:
The hostel is nice and modern where you stay to socialize. The room was kinda too hot, they need to turn in the air conditioning. Very friendly English speaking staff) they let us store our bags there before AND after checkout all day. They also give you pasta for dinner, which was actually really good.  The bar was a little more expensive though.

Basically the only downside is the room being too warm and 1 bathroom per 8 people but you get what you pay for for ‚Ç¨22/night. I would stay here again if I was in Rome but only the 4 or 6 person room.

name: Yellow Bar
review_text:
Good location walking and (I think) that there's a couple buys stops that are also very close,maybe a few blocks. I thought it was very odd at first and my friend thought that the receptionist was joking that both of our rooms were in different buildings across the street of the check-in. In that building there was this "play area" they called it. It was bad. Big jenga and I bunch of horrible bean bags. It was a nice area to chill though. Also a kitchen for us to use. Updated appliances,nice big table in the centre.  Although my space of when I made some good was taken over by a large group of 10, was a bit rude espically because they didn't ask. I know it was just me but still. Just a bit annoying, nothing the yellow could've done because it's not really their problem (in my mind). 3 restraunts extremely close, including their bar. Fyi the bar is pricey.

One of the bathrooms to my female 6 dorm had a dirty floor and when I took a shower the drain would clog up.  So i was standing in dirty water during my shower. But I did like the set up of my floor. Espically that there were 5 mirrors along the wall with chairs, hair dryers, and a long bar as a table to do makeup or something. In my room the bunk beds were different from any of the pictures, a bit creaky  to go up and down. The storage lockers were underneath the beds, but don't forget to bring your own lock. They probably sell them too for a fee but I didn't bother. The also give a little sequirity safe box near the door for every bed.

Some little things I didn't like but over all was a good experience.

review_text: This was my first hostel experience and it was an amazing one! I was traveling alone for the first time but never felt alone my entire stay. The staff were super nice minus the maid service they had that was so loud every time they entered the room. But I must say that the maid service did an amazing job because they fully cleaned the room every day. Our bathroom stayed spotless. It was so amazing having a bar literally across the street. I loved the staff at the bar and if you purchased your room through the-yellow directly you got discounts which is always amazing. The club they had downstairs was pretty cool too. I stayed in 2 other hostels since my first stay here at the yellow and not one has topped it. By far the greatest. Oh! it was pretty cool they did tours of Roma too, I wasn't able to do any as I already pre-booked tours but from what I heard they were pretty good.

Este hostel tiene una cocina muy linda y con bastantes utensillos para cocinar, una sala para relajarse con puff, una compu y tambien tiene un cuarto donde se puede dejar el equipaje. Lo malo era que el bar del hostel era muy caro. La musica estaba buena y todos los dias habia una banda diferente y despues de las 12 de la noche hay un dj. La ubicacion es ideal, ya que esta proximo a la terminal.
review_text_translated: It was a beautiful experience in Rome, the hostel was very clean and the staff always helping in everything we needed.This hostel has a very nice kitchen and with enough cooking utensillos, a room to relax with Puff, a computer and also has a room where you can leave the luggage.The bad thing was that the hostel bar was very expensive.The music was good and every day there was a different band and after 12 at night there is a DJ.The location is ideal, since it is next to the terminal.

name: Yellow Bar
review_text:
This place was nuts. Me and my roommate were travelling from Vancouver Island Canada, and we had to book on a dime in Rome and this place came up on every search engine as the top rated for a cheap price. They didn't have any standard rooms left but we booked through the hostels website so we got a discount on the private rooms. So worth the money, its like a hotel room (rooms are small still) but your getting all the social connectivity of a hostel. You also get a free Bracelet that gets you 20% of drinks and food at the bar/CLUB. That's right a CLUB, its literally right in the next building over. (there are three separate buildings located across the street from each other), Complementary meals (dinner not all day), free tours and discounts on others. They have games rooms, lounge rooms, you name it.

Ultimately. If you are coming here expect the coolest atmosphere and awesome crowd to party, relax, or tour with.  This is the place, every night is a different event; such as karaoke, beer pong competitions, etc.

Showers are pretty tidy, temperature wasn't an issue in early august, staff was fantastic, they didn't have any problems with us showing up late for check in.

name: Yellow Bar
review_text:
Sir Toby's is a wonderful, quaint hostel with a great social environment and extremely pleasant staff. The facilities are very clean and kept presentable at all times. I would absolutely recommend this place to anyone visiting Prague.

Pros:
-Staff; I had the pleasure of meeting several members of the staff and all were pleasant. 2 that stand out for me were Clemence (reception) and Nick (bartender). They made my experience there truly memorable and were always willing to go above and beyond to help with anything my group needed.
-Facilities; Sir Toby's was aesthetically please in all regards from the underground pub and social areas, to the reception office, and the garden/backyard. The rooms were also pleasant and everything was clean, including the bathrooms.
-Location; A very cheap Uber ride to Old Town Square and/or immediate access to the trams/buses makes the location optimum for travelers, especially if you want to be away from the inner city noise, but close enough that it's not a mission to get to. Uber to/from the airport is also cheap for a 30 minute ride.

Cons:
A/C; Although at night it can get pretty cool, sometimes you need just a little more on hot summer days. The room we were in had no A/C. Luckily the staff did provide us with 2 fans, but it was a 6 person dorm. Couldn't imagine what the 12 person dorm could be like.

review_text: Great vibe and location! The staff is so friendly. Our room was a little bit noisy since it was facing the street where the bar is.

name: Yellow Bar
review_text: The Yellow was a wonderful hostel, it was clean and they had towels available to borrow. The staff was friendly both at the hostel and the bar. The hostel felt very safe. The yellow bar was amazing, it was such a great time at night, the music, the atmosphere, the cheap drinks and dancing. In the morning you can have a cheap breakfast at the bar and the hostel is a 5 minutes walk from the Termini station and not too far from the Colosseum. Would definitely stay again!

name: Yellow Bar
review_text: Overall a very good experience! Not sure why I read reviews that said this place was "dirty" because my room was very very clean as much as a 3-4 star hotel. Only thing is if you are a solo traveler you have to really be friendly to enjoy it here as this place is more of a hotel than a hostel that creates a family feel. During the day I did all the walking tours and I would recommend each of them separately but not all on the same day (what I did). I walked for 12 hours straight and my legs were going to explode and I'm a young adult who goes to the gym 3-4 times a week. Finally, the bar is very cool. Cheap drinks and the bartenders are really charismatic! The people are very friendly as well and I met some awesome people and made a night of it. They have cool live music and a set list every night. The Red Hot Chili Peppers cover band was rocking!! Thanks for a great stay in Rome!

name: Yellow Bar
review_text:
I stayed in a private room and had a great experience. The bar/club across the street is open till 4am and actually has some pretty decent food in the day time. Make sure to book on their site so you get 20% off the booze.

Location is also great about two blocks from the metro and a 10 minute walk to Termani the main transit station.

review_text: The yellow has some iffy things about it, but over all our experience was very memorable (shoutout to our boy Filip). The breakfast, lunch, and dinner that they serve is very good (shoutout to marco) for what you're paying. The hostel offers many things like a cooking class, bike tours and much more. My friends and i took the cooking class and we had such an amazing time, Marco was very fun, and an amazing cook. The staff is very welcoming however there are some people that just aren't. Marco, Filip, and the woman who works in the bar for breakfast are really great! Also the people working in the hair salon are very very fun! If i go to rome again ill be staying here...

Best regards

name: Yellow Bar
review_text: Locale molto carino ampio ma sempre affollato (soprattutto di turisti). Unica pecca i buttafuori all'esterno del locale che, con maniere in alcuni casi poco cortesi e con un italiano stentato, ti invitano insistentemente a non sostare all'esterno nei paraggi del locale, nemmeno per il tempo di una sigaretta. Capisco che fanno solo il loro lavoro ma delle volte un po' educazione e cortesia non guastano
owner_answer: Grazie Alessio per la sua recensione. Lo Yellow √® un locale internazionale e applica una politica molto restrittiva riguardo gli schiamazzi. Basta una persona che rimane fuori a fumare ed in pochi minuti diventa un gruppo. Abbiamo camere ai piani superiori e vicini che la notte vogliono giustamente dormire, non impediamo a nessuno di fumare all'esterno ma gli chiediamo di farlo in fondo alla strada dove ci sono solo uffici, i quali di notte non sono abitati. I buttafuori non sono scortesi ma semplicemente insistenti con chi si sente al di sopra di tali regole. Ora sai il motivo e spero che d'ora in avanti non avrai bisogno di essere richiamato dal buttafuori, il quale parla benissimo: francese, inglese, spagnolo ed italiano magari non perfetto.
review_text_translated: Very nice large but always crowded place (especially of tourists).The only flaw the bouncers outside the place which, with manners in some cases not very courteous and with a stunted Italian, insistently invite you not to stop outside the comparison of the place, not even for the time of a cigarette.I understand that they only do their job but sometimes a little education and courtesy do not spoil
